"{\"uid\": \"en.wikipedia.org-wiki-2024_Summer_Olympics_boxing_controversy\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Theboxingcontroversy at the2024 Summer Olympic Gamesin Paris involved two female boxers:AlgerianImane KhelifandLin Yu-TingofTaiwan.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 55, \"end\": 60, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.213634041718456e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their eligibility to compete in the women's boxing events at theParis Olympic Gameswas questioned based on false allegations that they were not female.\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[1][2][3]  Both athletes had previously been disqualified from the2023 IBA Women's World Championshipsby theRussian-runInternational Boxing Association(IBA).\", \"from\": 284, \"to\": 441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 355, \"end\": 358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 417, \"end\": 423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.006710175466401e-25, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[1]The IBA claimed the disqualifications were based on unspecified \\\"gender tests\\\", which theInternational Olympic Committee(IOC) later determined were \\\"completely arbitrary\\\", \\\"illegitimate\\\", and \\\"lacked credibility.\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 448, \"end\": 451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 565, \"end\": 568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[4]In the lead-up to the Paris Games, the IOC cleared both athletes to compete.\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 699, \"end\": 702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[5]  The controversy escalated following an August 1 match in Paris, where Khelif faced Italian boxerAngela Carini.\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 798, \"end\": 803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.213634041718456e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 824, \"end\": 831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\", \"score\": 0.6495895983420203, \"rank\": 0.5385048697216683, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[1]After two head blows, Carini withdrew from the match, prompting widespread media speculation about Khelif's gender eligibility.\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 876, \"end\": 882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.999999996144652, \"rank\": 3.855185563472381e-09, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[6]  Although neither Khelif nor Lin aretransgender, the controversy became closely linked to broader public debates about trans women'sinclusion in women's sports.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[2][7][3][8]Several public figures, including then U.S. presidential candidateDonald Trump[9]and authorJ.\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1250, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"K. Rowling,[10]referenced the incident in political commentary about women in sports, often incorrectly suggesting Khelif wastransgender.\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"National sporting bodies fromAlgeriaandTaiwanissued strong defences of their athletes who were facing harassment over their eligibility as women to compete,[11][12]while the IOC reaffirmed the two athletes' eligibility.\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[13]  The incident occurred amid ongoing disputes between theIOC, which oversees theOlympic Games, and theIBA, boxing's long-time global governing body.\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[14]The IBA had been expelled from the Olympic movement in 2023 due to governance concerns.\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1852, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1769, \"end\": 1772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[15]While broader issues had already strained the relationship, the controversy surrounding Khelif and Lin was cited by some commentators as further illustrating the IBA's governance problems, particularly regarding athlete eligibility procedures.\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 2099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2018, \"end\": 2021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[16][17]  Prior to the 2024 Olympic Games, both Lin and Khelif had established themselves as prominent competitors in women's boxing.\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lin won gold medals in her weight class at the2018and2022AIBA Women's World Championships,[18]while Khelif secured a silver medal at the2022 World Championshipsand a gold medal at the2022 African Amateur Boxing Championships.\", \"from\": 2233, \"to\": 2458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2421, \"end\": 2457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Amateur_Boxing_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"African Amateur Boxing Championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Amateur_Boxing_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Amateur_Boxing_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[19]  Both athletes also competed at the2020 Tokyo Olympics, but did not medal, with Khelif reaching the quarterfinal stage.\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[20][21]  TheInternational Boxing Association(IBA), formerly known as AIBA (Association Internationale de Boxe Amateur), has historically served as the international governing body for amateur and professional boxing competitions.\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2812, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[22]  In 2006,Wu Ching-kuowas elected as the president of the association.\", \"from\": 2812, \"to\": 2886, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[23]During the 2010s under Wu's leadership, the organisation came under increasing scrutiny, with widespread allegations of financial mismanagement, political interference, and irregularities in judging.\", \"from\": 2886, \"to\": 3089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2913, \"end\": 2915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emperor_Wu_of_Han\", \"score\": 0.8818857375282311, \"rank\": 0.08843047188167531, \"text\": \"Wu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emperor_Wu_of_Han\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emperor_Wu_of_Han\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[24][25][26]These concerns culminated in the International Olympic Committee (IOC) suspending its recognition of the IBA in 2019, citing serious governance failures and a lack of transparency.\", \"from\": 3089, \"to\": 3281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3134, \"end\": 3171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3206, \"end\": 3209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[27]In response, the association issued lifetime bans to Wu Ching-kuo and electedGafur Rakhimovas the new president in November 2018.\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 3414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3338, \"end\": 3350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wu_Ching-kuo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wu Ching-kuo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wu_Ching-kuo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wu_Ching-kuo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[28][29]In 2020,Umar Kremlevwas elected as president of the IBA.\", \"from\": 3414, \"to\": 3478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3474, \"end\": 3477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[30]  Under Kremlev's leadership, the organisation faced further criticism over allegedRussianstate influence.\", \"from\": 3478, \"to\": 3588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Observers pointed to the IBA's sponsorship arrangements withGazprom, a Russian state-owned energy company, and raised concerns about the independence of its governance and decision-making processes.\", \"from\": 3589, \"to\": 3787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3614, \"end\": 3617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 3660, \"end\": 3667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.6426804017878461, \"rank\": 0.5548226399809449, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[31]  In June 2023, after repeated warnings and failed reform efforts, the IOC voted to formally expel the IBA from the Olympic movement.\", \"from\": 3787, \"to\": 3924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3862, \"end\": 3865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3894, \"end\": 3897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[24]In its decision, the IOC cited serious problems with the IBA's governance, highlighting particular concerns about political interference, financial control, and the integrity of officiating and judging at international boxing events.\", \"from\": 3924, \"to\": 4161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3949, \"end\": 3952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3985, \"end\": 3988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[32]  During theIBA Women's World Boxing Championshipsin March 2023, both Lin and Khelif were disqualified by theIBAmid-tournament after allegedly failing to meet eligibility criteria related to gender verification.\", \"from\": 4161, \"to\": 4376, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[33]  Imane Khelifcompeted for the gold medal in the finals.\", \"from\": 4376, \"to\": 4436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, she was disqualified shortly before her gold medal bout against People's Republic of China boxerYang Liu.\", \"from\": 4437, \"to\": 4551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[citation needed]This disqualification happened three days after Khelif defeatedAzalia Amineva[ru], a previously unbeaten Russian prospect, restoring the Russian boxer's undefeated record.\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4705, \"end\": 4712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.6426804017878461, \"rank\": 0.5548226399809449, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[34]The IBA claimed the disqualifications were based on unspecified \\\"gender tests\\\", which theInternational Olympic Committee(IOC) later determined were \\\"completely arbitrary\\\", \\\"illegitimate\\\", and \\\"lacked credibility.\", \"from\": 4739, \"to\": 4955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4747, \"end\": 4750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 4864, \"end\": 4867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[4][35][36]Uzbekistani boxerNavbakhor Khamidovawas awarded the bronze medal over Khelif.\", \"from\": 4955, \"to\": 5044, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[37]  In 2023,Umar Kremlev, president of the IBA, claimed that the disqualifications had occurred becauseDNA tests\\\"proved they hadXY chromosomes\\\".\", \"from\": 5044, \"to\": 5190, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5089, \"end\": 5092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[38][39]The Washington Poststated, \\\"It remains unclear what standards Khelif andLin Yu-tingfailed [in 2023] to lead to the disqualifications\\\",[39][38]adding \\\"There never has been evidence that [...] Khelif [...] had XY chromosomes or elevated levels of testosterone.\", \"from\": 5190, \"to\": 5456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[39]The IBA did not reveal the testing methodology, stating the \\\"specifics remain confidential\\\".\", \"from\": 5456, \"to\": 5553, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5465, \"end\": 5468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[40]At the time, Khelif said the ruling meant having \\\"characteristics that mean I can not box with women\\\", but said she was the victim of a \\\"big conspiracy\\\" regarding the disqualification.\", \"from\": 5553, \"to\": 5741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[41]She initially appealed to theCourt of Arbitration for Sportbut the appeal was terminated since Khelif could not pay the procedural costs.\", \"from\": 5741, \"to\": 5882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[42][43]  In late July 2024, both Lin and Khelif were officially deemed eligible to compete at the2024 Summer Olympic Gamesby theInternational Olympic Committee(IOC).\", \"from\": 5882, \"to\": 6048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[44]In a statement, the IOC said \\\"All athletes participating in the boxing tournament of the Olympic Games Paris 2024 comply with the competition's eligibility and entry regulations, as well as all applicable medical regulations in accordance with rules 1.4 and 3.1 of the Paris 2024 Boxing Unit.\", \"from\": 6048, \"to\": 6344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6072, \"end\": 6075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6332, \"end\": 6338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.006710175466401e-25, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[44]  The announcement attracted widespread attention and criticism online.\", \"from\": 6344, \"to\": 6420, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[45][46]Shortly after the IOC's announcement, theInternational Boxing Association(IBA) issued a statement criticising the decision, citing concerns around the IOC's handling of competitive fairness and athlete safety.\", \"from\": 6420, \"to\": 6637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6446, \"end\": 6449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6579, \"end\": 6582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[47]The IBA reaffirmed its March 2023 decision to disqualify Lin and Khelif from the2023 Women's World Boxing Championships, citing the athletes' failure to meet the eligibility criteria for women's competition.\", \"from\": 6637, \"to\": 6848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6645, \"end\": 6648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IBA clarified that Khelif and Lin \\\"did not undergo a testosterone examination but were subject to a separate and recognized test, whereby the specifics remain confidential\\\", and further alleged that they \\\"were found to have competitive advantages over other female competitors\\\".\", \"from\": 6849, \"to\": 7131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6853, \"end\": 6856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[48][better\\u00a0source\\u00a0needed]  The following day, the IOC released their own statement in response, stating that the IBA's decision was \\\"sudden and arbitrary\\\" and \\\"without any due process\\\".\", \"from\": 7131, \"to\": 7317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7182, \"end\": 7185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 7245, \"end\": 7248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC further stated:  According to the IBA minutes available on their website, this decision was initially taken solely by the IBA Secretary General and CEO.\", \"from\": 7318, \"to\": 7478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7322, \"end\": 7325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 7360, \"end\": 7363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 7448, \"end\": 7451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IBA Board only ratified it afterward and only subsequently requested that a procedure to follow in similar cases in the future be established and reflected in the IBA Regulations.\", \"from\": 7479, \"to\": 7662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7483, \"end\": 7486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The minutes also say that the IBA should \\\"establish a clear procedure on gender testing\\\".\", \"from\": 7663, \"to\": 7752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7693, \"end\": 7696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[49]  The IOC has suggested that the 2023 disqualifications may have been politically motivated, particularly in Khelif's case, as her removal followed a victory over a Russian boxer.\", \"from\": 7752, \"to\": 7935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7762, \"end\": 7765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 7921, \"end\": 7928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.6426804017878461, \"rank\": 0.5548226399809449, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[33]This allegation emerged amid broader criticisms of the IBA's leadership under Kremlev and the organisation's alleged close ties to Russian state interests.\", \"from\": 7935, \"to\": 8094, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7994, \"end\": 7997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 8070, \"end\": 8077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.6426804017878461, \"rank\": 0.5548226399809449, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language_in_Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[50]  On 1 August 2024, Imane Khelif competed against Italian boxerAngela Cariniin the women's boxing welterweight division at the Paris Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 8094, \"to\": 8245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8118, \"end\": 8130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 8148, \"end\": 8155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\", \"score\": 0.6495895983420203, \"rank\": 0.5385048697216683, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[51]Forty-six seconds into the match, following two head blows delivered by Khelif, Carini withdrew from the bout and appeared visibly distressed.\", \"from\": 8245, \"to\": 8391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8329, \"end\": 8335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.999999996144652, \"rank\": 3.855185563472381e-09, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[52]She declined to shake hands with Khelif, a gesture that drew immediate media attention.\", \"from\": 8391, \"to\": 8482, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[51]Speaking to reporters later, Carini stated that she had \\\"never felt a punch like this,\\\" prompting widespread speculation about the nature of Khelif's strength and gender eligibility.\", \"from\": 8482, \"to\": 8668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8515, \"end\": 8521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.999999996144652, \"rank\": 3.855185563472381e-09, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[52]  The match quickly became the subject of intense online debate.\", \"from\": 8668, \"to\": 8736, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[51]Several public figures, includingJ.\", \"from\": 8736, \"to\": 8775, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"K. Rowling,Elon MuskandLogan Paul, commented on the incident, incorrectly claiming that Khelif was biologically male or transgender.\", \"from\": 8776, \"to\": 8908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8776, \"end\": 8778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Kirkpatrick\", \"score\": 0.9999945788196392, \"rank\": 5.085224437916378e-06, \"text\": \"K.\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Kirkpatrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Kirkpatrick\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[51][53][54]Misinformation circulated rapidly across social media platforms, with posts often misrepresenting Khelif's background and eligibility status.\", \"from\": 8908, \"to\": 9061, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[55]  On 2 August, the IOC released an official statement affirming that both Khelif and Lin were women eligible to compete, according to their passports and their histories competing in women's boxing.\", \"from\": 9061, \"to\": 9263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9084, \"end\": 9087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[56][57]The IOC also reiterated that the disqualifications at the2023 IBA Women's World Championshipshad been conducted without due process, criticising the IBA's approach in handling the matter as \\\"contrary to good governance\\\".\", \"from\": 9263, \"to\": 9491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9275, \"end\": 9278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 9333, \"end\": 9336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 9420, \"end\": 9423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[58]IOC PresidentThomas Bachwent further to describe the backlash against the athletes as part of a \\\"politically motivated... culture war\\\".\", \"from\": 9491, \"to\": 9630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[59]He linked the issue to a wider, Russian-led campaign against the IOC and the Olympic movement.\", \"from\": 9630, \"to\": 9728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9699, \"end\": 9702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[60]The IOC expressed support for both athletes, denouncing the harassment, hate speech, and misinformation they had faced online and in the media.\", \"from\": 9728, \"to\": 9875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9736, \"end\": 9739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[59][60]  In the days following the match, Carini clarified that her decision not to shake hands had not been intentional and expressed regret over the way the bout had been portrayed.\", \"from\": 9875, \"to\": 10059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9918, \"end\": 9924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.999999996144652, \"rank\": 3.855185563472381e-09, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[61]She further stated that she did not believe Khelif had acted improperly during the competition.\", \"from\": 10059, \"to\": 10158, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[61]  TheAlgerian Olympic Committeeissued several statements affirming Khelif's eligibility and criticising what they described as \\\"baseless attacks\\\" and \\\"unethical targeting\\\" on her reputation.\", \"from\": 10158, \"to\": 10352, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[62][63]Algerian officials emphasised that Khelif had passed all required eligibility checks conducted by the International Olympic Committee (IOC) and accused some foreign media outlets and commentators of engaging in \\\"baseless propaganda.\", \"from\": 10352, \"to\": 10592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10360, \"end\": 10368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.999931890833391, \"rank\": 6.811380548853391e-05, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 10462, \"end\": 10499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[62]In a statement posted toX, Algerian Sports MinisterAbderrahmane Hammadsaid \\\"Our great Iman Khelif is under attack from an organization that has no legitimacy with IOC.\", \"from\": 10592, \"to\": 10764, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10683, \"end\": 10687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yiman_people\", \"score\": 0.9999999008932767, \"rank\": 9.91071830123067e-08, \"text\": \"Iman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yiman_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yiman_people\"}, {\"begin\": 10760, \"end\": 10763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Incredible resources are used to legally pursue and hold accountable anyone who dares to threaten or defame her.\", \"from\": 10765, \"to\": 10877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[64]  Although neither Lin nor Khelif are transgender, the controversy surrounding their participation in the Paris Olympics became closely associated with broader culture wars overtransgender inclusion in sports.\", \"from\": 10877, \"to\": 11091, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[65][51]Public discourse conflated questions of the two athletes' gender eligibility with debates abouttransgenderathletes.\", \"from\": 11091, \"to\": 11214, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[66][8]  Online misinformation contributed significantly to the visibility and intensity of the controversy.\", \"from\": 11214, \"to\": 11322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Social media posts misidentifying Khelif as transgender or biologically male circulated widely.\", \"from\": 11323, \"to\": 11418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[53][55]2024 U.S. presidential candidateTrumpused the controversy to reinforce election campaign rhetoric advocating for restrictions on women's sports participation based on assigned sex at birth, while authorJ.\", \"from\": 11418, \"to\": 11630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"K. Rowlingdescribed the situation as emblematic of a \\\"new men's rights movement\\\" displacing women.\", \"from\": 11631, \"to\": 11729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11631, \"end\": 11633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Kirkpatrick\", \"score\": 0.9999945788196392, \"rank\": 5.085224437916378e-06, \"text\": \"K.\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Kirkpatrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Kirkpatrick\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[67][68]  Commentators have noted the harm to the individual athletes involved, who have been forced to have their personal medical histories discussed in the public arena.\", \"from\": 11729, \"to\": 11901, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[69]  Scholars have also observed that the accusations directed at Khelif reflect a broader pattern in which athletes withvariations in sexual characteristicsare more likely to face scrutiny under gender eligibility rules, often in ways that reinforce narrow definitions of womanhood.\", \"from\": 11901, \"to\": 12185, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[70][71]Critics have noted that while organising sport along binary gender lines has helped preserve space for women's athletic achievements, it often disadvantages athletes who fall outside dominant perceptions of how female athletes should look or perform.\", \"from\": 12185, \"to\": 12443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[70][72][73]Such challenges have particularly affected women of colour from theGlobal South.\", \"from\": 12443, \"to\": 12535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[74][75][76]The episode has drawn comparisons to previous controversies in elite women's sports involvingCaster SemenyaandDutee Chand, athletes with differences in sex development (DSDs) who were subjected to eligibility challenges and public scrutiny.\", \"from\": 12535, \"to\": 12787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[77][72]  Khelif has made several public statements defending her eligibility and speaking about the personal toll of the controversy.\", \"from\": 12787, \"to\": 12921, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[78]During the Games, Khelif spoke about the scrutiny and pressure she faced following the match against Carini: \\\"This has effects, massive effects.\", \"from\": 12921, \"to\": 13069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13026, \"end\": 13032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.999999996144652, \"rank\": 3.855185563472381e-09, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It can destroy people, it can kill people's thoughts, spirit and mind.\", \"from\": 13070, \"to\": 13140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It can divide people.\", \"from\": 13141, \"to\": 13162, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And because of that, I ask them to refrain from bullying.\", \"from\": 13163, \"to\": 13220, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[72][79]  On 9 August, after winning the gold medal in the women'swelterweight(66\\u00a0kg) boxing category, Khelif reaffirmed her eligibility: \\\"I am fully qualified to take part in this competition.\", \"from\": 13220, \"to\": 13414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am a woman like any other woman.\", \"from\": 13415, \"to\": 13449, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was born a woman, I lived a woman, I competed as a woman, there is no doubt about that.\", \"from\": 13450, \"to\": 13539, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[The detractors] are enemies of success, that is what I call them.\", \"from\": 13540, \"to\": 13606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that also gives my success a special taste because of these attacks.\", \"from\": 13607, \"to\": 13679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[78]  On 13 August 2024, Khelif filed a criminal complaint with French authorities, alleging aggravated cyber harassment against a number of public figures who had posted to social media platformX (formerly Twitter), namingJ.\", \"from\": 13679, \"to\": 13905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13744, \"end\": 13750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9466742421992451, \"rank\": 0.0563038239297108, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 13887, \"end\": 13894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 0.9999999945284799, \"rank\": 5.471749977829424e-09, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"K. RowlingandElon Muskspecifically.\", \"from\": 13906, \"to\": 13941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[80]In November 2024, Khelif also took legal action against French media, which had published claims that Khelif hadXY chromosomes.\", \"from\": 13941, \"to\": 14072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14001, \"end\": 14007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9466742421992451, \"rank\": 0.0563038239297108, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[81]  Lin has also commented on public scrutiny about her gender.\", \"from\": 14072, \"to\": 14137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[My appearance] draws a lot of attention.\", \"from\": 14138, \"to\": 14180, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes when I go to the restroom, I get asked 'Is that the right one?'\", \"from\": 14181, \"to\": 14254, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then I would tell them I am a woman...\", \"from\": 14255, \"to\": 14293, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not control what others say...\", \"from\": 14294, \"to\": 14330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not have to cater to stereotypes.\", \"from\": 14331, \"to\": 14369, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[82]  During the Games, Lin largely avoided addressing the eligibility controversy and deactivated her social media after her first Olympic bout.\", \"from\": 14369, \"to\": 14515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[83]Speaking about the topic after winning the gold medal in her category, Lin stated: \\\"As an elite athlete, during the competition it's important to shut myself off from social media and focus.\", \"from\": 14515, \"to\": 14709, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course I heard some of the information through my coach but I did not pay too much mind to it.\", \"from\": 14710, \"to\": 14807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was invited by the IOC to participate in the games and this is what I focused on.\", \"from\": 14808, \"to\": 14891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14829, \"end\": 14832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[84]  The controversy involving Khelif and Lin occurred amid ongoing tensions between theInternational Olympic Committee(IOC) and theInternational Boxing Association(IBA).\", \"from\": 14891, \"to\": 15063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15013, \"end\": 15016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[85][32]The relationship between the two organisations had been strained since 2019, when the IOC suspended its recognition of the IBA due to concerns over governance, financial mismanagement, and irregularities in refereeing and judging.\", \"from\": 15063, \"to\": 15301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15157, \"end\": 15160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 15194, \"end\": 15197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[31]  The disqualifications of Khelif and Lin during the2023 IBA Women's World Championshipsbecame a key point of contention between the two organisations.\", \"from\": 15301, \"to\": 15456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the lead-up to the 2024 Paris Games, the IBA objected to the IOC's decision to allow both athletes to compete despite their earlier disqualifications.\", \"from\": 15457, \"to\": 15610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15501, \"end\": 15504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 15521, \"end\": 15524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[86]In response, the IOC stated that the disqualifications had been carried out without due process and were not in line with established medical or eligibility standards.\", \"from\": 15610, \"to\": 15781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15631, \"end\": 15634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[87][33]In a public statement, IOC PresidentThomas Bachalso referred to the IBA's criticisms of Khelif and Lin as stemming from a \\\"fake news campaign from Russia.\", \"from\": 15781, \"to\": 15943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15857, \"end\": 15860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 15936, \"end\": 15942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.934521299943055e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[88]  In February 2025, following the issuance of U.S. PresidentDonald Trump'sExecutive Order 14201, titled \\\"Keeping Men Out of Women's Sports,\\\" the IBA filed a complaint with the Office of the Attorney General of Switzerland (OAG).\", \"from\": 15943, \"to\": 16176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16093, \"end\": 16096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 16158, \"end\": 16169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.569624744656847e-14, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 16171, \"end\": 16174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Auditor_General_of_Canada\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7912777470322516e-70, \"text\": \"OAG\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Auditor_General_of_Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Auditor_General_of_Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[89]The complaint contested the IOC's decision to allow Khelif and Lin to compete at the Paris Olympics, alleging that the IOC had disregarded eligibility criteria and undermined athlete safety.\", \"from\": 16176, \"to\": 16370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16208, \"end\": 16211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 16299, \"end\": 16302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[89]  Shortly after the IBA was expelled from the Olympic Movement in 2023, some members broke away to formWorld Boxing.\", \"from\": 16370, \"to\": 16490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16394, \"end\": 16397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 16420, \"end\": 16436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1264288869076062e-23, \"text\": \"Olympic Movement\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[90]Between 2023 and 2025, the organisation had hoped to be the IBA's replacement as international governing body for boxing.\", \"from\": 16490, \"to\": 16615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16554, \"end\": 16557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[91]  During the Paris Games, the IOC reiterated that the IBA's recognition has been withdrawn and stated that national boxing federations would need to identify an alternative governing body for boxing to remain on the programme at the2028 Los Angeles Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 16615, \"to\": 16882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16649, \"end\": 16652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 16673, \"end\": 16676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.375888511629139e-11, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[87]  In March 2025, the IOC provisionally recognised World Boxing.\", \"from\": 16882, \"to\": 16949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16907, \"end\": 16910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 16942, \"end\": 16948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.006710175466401e-25, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[92][93]The IOC also confirmed that boxing would be included on the programme for the2028 Olympic Games, with World Boxing provisionally serving as the Olympics' recognised international federation for boxing.\", \"from\": 16949, \"to\": 17158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16961, \"end\": 16964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 17065, \"end\": 17071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.006710175466401e-25, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[94]  In November 2024, Lin pulled out of competing at the World Boxing Cup Finals inSheffield, England, following questions from organisers over her gender eligibility.\", \"from\": 17158, \"to\": 17327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17254, \"end\": 17261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9999958080149197, \"rank\": 3.6569597602577517e-06, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[95]  Taiwan's Sports Administration stated that Lin met all eligibility criteria and had been cleared by the IOC to compete in Paris, but that World Boxing had raised new questions regarding her eligibility.\", \"from\": 17327, \"to\": 17535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17333, \"end\": 17339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999998753992, \"rank\": 1.2465113355629057e-10, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 17437, \"end\": 17440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4522877078836602e-60, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 17455, \"end\": 17460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.213634041718456e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 17477, \"end\": 17483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.006710175466401e-25, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[96]They criticised World Boxing for lacking clear regulatory protections and for failing to implement adequate confidentiality procedures to safeguard Lin's medical information.\", \"from\": 17535, \"to\": 17713, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[96]According to their statement, Lin offered to undergo a medical examination in the UK, but the proposal was not accepted.\", \"from\": 17713, \"to\": 17837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17799, \"end\": 17801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9989668724108626, \"rank\": 0.0010341960087748392, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[96]To prevent further reputational harm, Lin and her team chose to withdraw from the event.\", \"from\": 17837, \"to\": 17929, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[95]  In March 2025, World Boxing's president,Boris van der Vorst, announced that recommendations from a formal investigation into the gender eligibility controversy that arose during the Paris Olympics were expected \\\"soon\\\".\", \"from\": 17929, \"to\": 18153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17956, \"end\": 17962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.006710175466401e-25, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}, {\"begin\": 17989, \"end\": 17994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00fcrst\", \"score\": 0.5617140664946932, \"rank\": 0.7738439306359098, \"text\": \"Vorst\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00fcrst\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00fcrst\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[97]He confirmed that a working group, in coordination with the organisation's medical committee, was developing a comprehensive policy on sex, age, and weight eligibility, drawing on expert input from around the world.\", \"from\": 18153, \"to\": 18372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[98]  In May, World Boxing's executive board released updated rules mandating sex testing for all athletes, stating \\\"Athletes that are deemed to be male at birth, as evidenced by the presence of Y chromosome... or with a difference of sexual development (DSD) where male androgenization occurs, will be eligible to compete in the male category.\", \"from\": 18372, \"to\": 18716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18392, \"end\": 18398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.006710175466401e-25, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}, {\"begin\": 18627, \"end\": 18630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.300438428287892e-13, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes that are deemed to be female at birth... or with a DSD where male androgenization does not occur, will be eligible to compete in the female category.\", \"from\": 18717, \"to\": 18875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18777, \"end\": 18780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.300438428287892e-13, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[99]\", \"from\": 18875, \"to\": 18880, \"entities\": []}]}"